Ama was first listed as a [[census designated place]] in the [[2000 U.S. census]].<ref name=2000CensusLA>{{Cite web|first= |last= |authorlink=   |title= 2000 Census of Population - Population and Housing Unit Counts - Louisiana |publisher=United States Census Bureau|date= 2000|url=https://www2.census.gov/library/publications/2003/dec/phc-3-20.pdf|accessdate=}}</ref>

According to the [[2000 United States census]], there were 1,285 people residing in Ama.<ref name="GR2">{{cite web|url=https://www.census.gov |publisher=[[United States Census Bureau]] |accessdate=2008-01-31 |title=U.S. Census website }}</ref> By 2020, its population increased to 1,290.<ref name=":0" /> At the 2019 [[American Community Survey]], there were 79.8 males per 100 females and the median age among its population was 40.<ref>{{Cite web|title=2019 Demographic and Housing Estimates|url=https://data.census.gov/cedsci/table?q=Ama%20CDP,%20Louisiana%20population&tid=ACSDP5Y2019.DP05|url-status=live|access-date=2021-10-25|website=United States Census Bureau|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20211025160540/https://data.census.gov/cedsci/table?q=Ama%20CDP,%20Louisiana%20population&tid=ACSDP5Y2019.DP05 |archive-date=2021-10-25 }}</ref>

From 2010 census estimates to the 2020 census [[non-Hispanic or Latino whites]] and [[African Americans|Black or African Americans]] have remained the largest racial and ethnic groups in the CDP,<ref>{{Cite web|title=2010 Demographic and Housing Estimates|url=https://data.census.gov/cedsci/table?q=Ama%20CDP,%20Louisiana%20population&tid=ACSDP5Y2010.DP05|url-status=live|access-date=2021-10-25|website=United States Census Bureau|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20211025160646/https://data.census.gov/cedsci/table?q=Ama%20CDP,%20Louisiana%20population&tid=ACSDP5Y2010.DP05 |archive-date=2021-10-25 }}</ref><ref name=":0" /> although [[multiracial Americans]] were also prominent. In 2000, the Ama's racial and ethnic makeup was 64.9% [[White Americans|White]], 34.4% Black or African American, 0.16% [[Native Americans in the United States|American Indian and Alaska Native]], 0.16% [[Asian Americans|Asian]], 0.16% from some other race, 0.23% from two or more races, and 1.01% [[Hispanic and Latino Americans|Hispanic or Latino American]] of any race.

Economically, the median income for a household in the CDP was $57,794; the CDP's mean income for a household was $65,775, up from a median of $41,691 in 2000.<ref>{{Cite web|title=2019 Annual Income Estimates|url=https://data.census.gov/cedsci/table?q=Ama%20CDP,%20Louisiana%20median%20income&tid=ACSST5Y2019.S1901|url-status=live|access-date=2021-10-25|website=United States Census Bureau|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20211025160524/https://data.census.gov/cedsci/table?q=Ama%20CDP,%20Louisiana%20median%20income&tid=ACSST5Y2019.S1901 |archive-date=2021-10-25 }}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|title=2000 Median Household Income|url=https://data.census.gov/cedsci/table?q=Ama%20CDP,%20Louisiana%20median%20income&tid=DECENNIALSF32000.P053|url-status=live|access-date=2021-10-25|website=United States Census Bureau|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20211025160553/https://data.census.gov/cedsci/table?q=Ama%20CDP,%20Louisiana%20median%20income&tid=DECENNIALSF32000.P053 |archive-date=2021-10-25 }}</ref> Among its population, 9.5% were approximately at or below the poverty line; 1.9% of families were below the poverty line in 2019.<ref>{{Cite web|title=2019 Poverty Statistics|url=https://data.census.gov/cedsci/table?q=Ama%20CDP,%20Louisiana%20poverty&tid=ACSST5Y2019.S1701|url-status=live|access-date=2021-10-25|website=United States Census Bureau|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20211025160617/https://data.census.gov/cedsci/table?q=Ama%20CDP,%20Louisiana%20poverty&tid=ACSST5Y2019.S1701 |archive-date=2021-10-25 }}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|title=2019 Family Poverty Statistics|url=https://data.census.gov/cedsci/table?q=Ama%20CDP,%20Louisiana%20poverty&tid=ACSST5Y2019.S1702|url-status=live|access-date=2021-10-25|website=United States Census Bureau|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20211025160542/https://data.census.gov/cedsci/table?q=Ama%20CDP,%20Louisiana%20poverty&tid=ACSST5Y2019.S1702 |archive-date=2021-10-25 }}</ref>

